 form a bigger guild with an alliance from many other guilds?  I bring up nothing like name and leadership as I'm only looking to see if there is interest.  If you are lower ranked, you may not realize this yet, but once you hit over 30, you will see how hard it becomes to play without a bigger group and pool of players to choose and once you raid, then you will see how hard it is.  Which is why I am suggesting an alliance of many guilds and players to disband and form a bigger guild, one where we could find groups and do raids with an amount of player that amounts to more than running in on a suicide raid do to lack of assets.  Some guilds out there lack tanks, others lack casters, others healer and we all suffer, it's time that we unit what we have.  This would especially be usefull in high end game, 40+ when you start to raid the planes and such.<br>
<br>
If there are some with interest, please post.  I also ask my guild leader to do so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/29/01 6:33:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Eh, enchanters are nice ..</span><hr size=1> .. but it's nothing to disband a guild over.  In fact, the only things I can think of where one is required are some of the very high level fights where they charm mobs over and over and the tanks just go defensive turn by turn.  Bards and necros can mez, too.  Bards, in fact, are a lot more useful in a group than an enchanter, imho.  Shaman can both slow and root things off.  Paladins are pretty pathetic for damage output, but they make great ghetto-mez'ers.  There are lots of alternatives to enchanters.<br>
<br>
BTW, a nicely mixed 50 person guild can do every mob and zone in the game, just not all in the same day. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uprothall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prothall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/29/01 8:24:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ghetto Mez</span><hr size=1> <br>
The cookie cutter idea of a group seems to be what most people desire, that is warrior for a tank, cleric as main healer, enchanter as main mezzer, etc. However what people expectations are and what reality may be can sometimes collide. <br>
<br>
In another life, I can remember easily doing disco area of Sebillis with a druid (55+) as main healer and a Necromancer as main enchanter. Root also came in handy as well as another form of &quot;mez&quot;.  Is this most efficient? No. However it is effective given the circumstances.<br>
<br>
Do not discount bards either, they are very versed (well the ones that can play decently) in crowd control issues. <br>
<br>
I suppose the point im trying to come to is this, and to further back up what the previous poster indicated, that many, many things can be done without what you may consider to be the ideal group. Disbanding formations in order to form more &quot;cookie cutter&quot; guilds isnt the best way i feel, rather forming alliances with current guilds is a good idea.<br>
<br>
Regardless of what steps are taken, people will leave guilds often in pursuit of the bigger fish they want to catch when their small boat cannot handle the size of their...umm...fishing pole. I<br>
<br>
ts a natural part of Everquest sadly, especially those who feveriously pursue the high end game in lieu of any bonds or friendships they may have developed. <br>
<br>
Best Wishes!<br>
 <p><BR><center><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~abspara/Valanissigpic.jpg" height=90 width=350 </center></a><BR>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 3:50:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ghetto Mez</span><hr size=1> If it works for you, more power to you.<br>
<br>
For me, however, I belong to a small guild that wants to remain small. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umidwestpatriot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MidwestPatriot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/01 1:39:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> We are elven only  :^)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <br>
