William Shakespeare, Hamlet  <br></font>
</b>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/01 6:24:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We are elven only  :^)</span><hr size=1> Aye, this be true that if ye do not make allies with yer similarly aligned neighbors that yer guild may be doomed fer failure. I be suggesting to ye to pressure yer leaders to try to find allies in other guilds. I be one o' the leaders in me own guild and am presently werking on just that, fer i tink me guild is great and wish it be lasting fer as long as me being a citizen o' Norrath. Good luck to ye and may ye find way out o' yer predicament.<br>
<br>
Dhugal Forgefyre<br>
Society of Valor Councilman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/01 6:52:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We are elven only  :^)</span><hr size=1> My neighbors are all those who don't serve evil. Not guilding with your guild is racial discrimination and I would think mostly only evil would do such a thing as under the light all are the same. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/1/02 8:54:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/students/b/t/btk120/MOKONA.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ahem.</span><hr size=1> I've seen RP discrimination on both sides of the coin, thank you.<br>
<br>
As long as it's RP.<br>
<br>
 <p>--Antoin &lt;Shadow Dragoon&gt;
<br><i>"I'm glad to report that I'm the only pinnacle of evil in a 30-mile radius."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unakath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nakath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 3:06:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ahem.</span><hr size=1> well, i'll speak for my guild... if we were interested in being part of a big, mixed guild, we would still be on our old server.<br>
<br>
I know for a fact that a 2 group guild can experience 95+% of the game. This includes killing dragons, doing epic quests, etc.<br>
<br>
There are 2 main positive things that big guilds do: they increase the CHANCE that you will have the right people online to do a given quest or task and they increase the CHANCE that you will be grouped with someone who is accountable to player authorities.<br>
<br>
Large guilds have terrible problems however, that I wouldn't wish on my worst enemy. Loot Whoring, Whining, Cronyism, Nepotism, Internal Politics, etc etc etc.<br>
<br>
I say this: if you are 40+ and have 12-15 people that you trust on the server, make a guild with them, and enjoy the game. Go slowly and see everything. The game is huge and a lot of people just pass by things because they don't know they are there. <p>Nakath<BR>
The Esoteric Order</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 6:45:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ahem.</span><hr size=1> I don't speak for my guild when I say this, but I think an alliance of various guilds, perhaps with a shared website to link them and co-operative raids, would be interesting.  For those guilds who want to preserve their uniqueness but enjoy the benefits of broader opporunities it could be a great option.  But a mass guild of various things mashed together probably isn't in the cards.<br>
<br>
If you want this to happen that's great, start talking to leaders and arrange something.  But like a lot of ideas that get posted on this board, most starting with &quot;It's time to...&quot; this isn't going to go anywhere on the strength of just saying what should happen.  It takes someone willing to put in the time and effort to organize it and take responsibility for it.  That isn't me.  Is it you, Feneant?<br>
<br>
Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhelmgest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Helmgest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 8:57:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ahem.</span><hr size=1> There are a number of servers that have &quot;Guild Alliances&quot; on them.  Most come to be because the smaller guilds cannot compete with the &quot;Uber Guild&quot; and team up to put themselves on the same level.<br>
<br>
Druzzil Ro is the only one I have a link for:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.druzzilroalliance.com/">www.druzzilroalliance.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
FV won't have that problem, I think, since the few &quot;Ubers&quot; we have seem fairly well-natured and the population is so low that there should be no real reason to compete for spawns (I hope, anyway - we'll see what happens when several clerics need Ragefire).  <br>
<br>
The guild alliance idea could help here to coordinate the smaller guilds in raids, but this message board would seem to be more than sufficient for that task.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 12:01:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ahem.</span><hr size=1> Well, since most guilds have little to no interest, it probably won't happen.  My original thought was to have a guild with no real leader and the officers being the leaders from other guilds and a few others.  But even the guild alliance is not only a plausible solution, its needed.  Like pretty much everyone else, I have a list of item I wish to obtain but require more strenght then what I can muster, some items requiring rather complete raids.  From what I've seen, there have been very few raids, even of smaller and weaker zones, for some, the idea of forming a guild is just to say 'Hey, I run a guild', but then if nothing is done, the guild is basically just another chat channel and nothing more.<br>
<br>
As for what helmgest posted, see, it does make sense, they are 6 guilds formed together to have a better chance at getting what they need.  I've not heard of anyone getting an epic on this server, but I do know mine requires killing the queen of Chardok, 2 dragons, a spiroc lord and the Maestro and how many guilds on the server can say 'Hey, let's raid Chardok so our warriors can get their epics'.  Even if this is an RP server, I don't plan on being in Karnor from 45-60 killing the same mobs over and over wearing crafted till it rots off my body.<br>
<br>
There's a difference between being a small knit group of players and just waiting until you hit a wall and can't get any more gear, complete any new quests or hit any new zones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 11:05:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=976.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ahem.</span><hr size=1> <br>
There was a large alliance on the Prexus server known as &quot;Genesis&quot;.  The member-guilds changed a lot, and while there were a few alliance-level events, there was a lot more friction than there would have been if there wasn't an official alliance.<br>
<br>
There are a few problems with guild alliances.  The primary one being that there is still an &quot;Us vs Them&quot;.  And right next to that is the issue of communication -- the guild channel does a lot toward binding people closer together.<br>
